# Inventory UI Kit Rule

Reference design:
https://www.figma.com/design/gmroR89dCMJN6pgoLzuUPd/Inventory-Management-Dashboard--Community-?node-id=0-1&p=f&t=eulh6st6wbGjpqEs-0

## Core visual direction

- Use clean light surfaces with soft contrast and readable hierarchy.
- Keep radius consistent (10/12/16), thin borders, subtle shadows.
- Avoid heavy gradients and glossy glass effects.
- Keep spacing rhythm consistent: 8, 12, 16, 24.
- Prioritize scanability for tables, cards, filters, and KPI blocks.

## Page structure

- Header row: page title, then contextual actions on the right.
- Filter/toolbar row: compact controls, consistent input heights.
- Main content in cards/panels with equal internal paddings.
- Details pages: info card + media card + tabs + tab content.

## Components

- Buttons: primary solid, secondary ghost; no oversized pills.
- Tables: sticky/simple headers, clear row hover, no ALL CAPS headers.
- Forms: labels above fields, one visual style for all inputs/selects.
- Badges: neutral/info/success/warning/danger via muted backgrounds.
- Pagination: compact, same size and radius as toolbar controls.

## Interaction rules

- List rows navigate to details pages (prefer route over modal details).
- Keep edit mode inline on details pages where possible.
- Show loading, empty, and error states with the same card style.

## Number formatting

- Format quantities, currency, and totals consistently across all pages.
- Use readable separators and fixed precision per metric type.
